description:
{{sbc|Innate - Wolf:}} Starting at {{sbc|3:15}}, '''Wolf''' periodically marks a random large {{tip|monster}} within the enemy team's jungle for 180 seconds. The ''hunted'' camp is highlighted on the [[Map (League of Legends)|mini map]] to both teams. Once the ''hunted'' target is slain, '''Wolf''' will wait 45 seconds before selecting a new target. <br/>The type of monster that '''Wolf''' can mark changes based on '''Kindred's''' current stacks:
* {{sbc|0 :}} {{ui|Rift Scuttler}}
* {{sbc|1 – 3:}} {{ui|Rift Scuttler}}, {{ui|Crimson Raptor}}, {{ui|Gromp}}
* {{sbc|4 – 7:}} {{ui|Ancient Krug}}, {{ui|Blue Sentinel}}, {{ui|Greater Murk Wolf}}, or {{ui|Red Brambleback}}
* {{sbc|8 + :}} {{ui|Rift Herald}} or {{ui|Baron Nashor}}, {{ui|Dragon}} or {{ui|Elder Dragon}}

e1.notes:
* {{ii|Guinsoo's Rageblade}} does not prevent the '''additional''' damage from {{tip|critical strike|critically striking}}.
* If the target becomes {{tip|untargetable}}, {{tip|death|dies}}, or is too far away or no longer in {{tip|sight}} during the cast time, this ability will cancel and not pay its cost but still go on {{sti|cooldown}}.{{bug}}
* This ability cannot be cast on a target with ''Mounting Dread'' stacks.
